<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Downloading the Correct Drivers</h2>



<p>Printing is handled on Linux by the <a href=3D"https://wiki.archlinux.or=
g/title/CUPS" data-type=3D"URL" data-id=3D"https://wiki.archlinux.org/title=
/CUPS" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">CUPS</a> software in t=
he background. In order for CUPS to recognize your Printer correctly, you w=
ill need the appropriate drivers. For example, I have the Canon Pixma GM407=
0 model printer and without the official Printer drivers installed, it gets=
 listed as HP Designjet T920 which is obviously not the case.</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img decoding=3D"as=
ync" width=3D"1024" height=3D"693" src=3D"https://cdn.linuxfordevices.com/w=
p-content/uploads/2023/07/Printer-model-is-incorrectly-recognized-without-d=
rivers-1024x693.png.webp" alt=3D"Printer Model Is Incorrectly Recognized Wi=
thout Drivers" class=3D"wp-image-26212"><figcaption class=3D"wp-element-cap=
tion">Printer Model Is Incorrectly Recognized Without Drivers</figcaption><=
/figure>



<p>To download the correct drivers, visit the <a href=3D"https://in.canon/e=
n/support/search?q=3DPIXMA+GM4070" target=3D"_blank" data-type=3D"URL" data=
-id=3D"https://in.canon/en/support/search?q=3DPIXMA+GM4070" rel=3D"noreferr=
er noopener">official Canon website</a>, and search for the Model name of y=
our Printer. You can find the model name easily on the Printer itself, eith=
er on the front, or at the back of it.</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading=3D"laz=
y" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1024" height=3D"470" src=3D"https://cdn.linu=
xfordevices.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Search-for-your-Printer-model-on=
-the-official-website-1024x470.png.webp" alt=3D"Search For Your Printer Mod=
el On The Official Website" class=3D"wp-image-26214"><figcaption class=3D"w=
p-element-caption">Searching for Your Printer Model</figcaption></figure>



<p>Once you have found your Printer model, simply click on the blue hyperli=
nk, and you will be redirected to the driver page.</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img loading=3D"lazy=
" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1021" height=3D"837" src=3D"https://cdn.linux=
fordevices.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Download-the-appropriate-Linux-dr=
iver.png.webp" alt=3D"Download The Appropriate Linux Driver" class=3D"wp-im=
age-26215"><figcaption class=3D"wp-element-caption">Selecting the Linux Dri=
ver for Your Distribution</figcaption></figure>



<p>From the dropdown menu, select the Linux 64bit option, and then you will=
 see various options for your printer. If you are using Fedora/RHEL/OpenSUS=
E or any of its derivative distributions such as Alma Linux or Rocky Linux,=
 then simply download the latest <strong>IJ Printer Diver Ver. X.YY for Lin=
ux (rpm PackageArchive)</strong>. And if you are using Debian, Ubuntu, or a=
ny of their derivative Linux distribution such as Pop_OS, Linux Mint, etc.,=
 then download the IJ Printer Diver Ver. X.YY for Linux (Debian<strong> Pac=
kageArchive)</strong> file.</p><div class=3D"code-block code-block-2" style=
=3D"margin: 8px 0; clear: both; height: 250px;">
<div id=3D"dff5e9f6-d3ed-44f0-a9b9-9bac542719aa" class=3D"_ap_apex_ad" max-=
height=3D"250">
=09
</div>
