<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Installing the Canon Printer Drivers on Linu=
x</h2>



<p>Once the driver archive file is downloaded, we have to extract them. You=
 can easily do this from the command line by typing the following commands =
in the Terminal window of your respective distribution:</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-syntaxhighlighter-code "><div><div id=3D"highlighter=
_43434" class=3D"syntaxhighlighter  bash"><table border=3D"0" cellpadding=
=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"gutter"><div class=3D"line=
 number1 index0 alt2">1</div></td><td class=3D"code"><div class=3D"containe=
r"><div class=3D"line number1 index0 alt2"><code class=3D"bash functions">t=
ar</code> <code class=3D"bash plain">-xvf ~</code><code class=3D"bash plain=
">/Downloads/cnijfilter2-6</code><code class=3D"bash plain">.00-1-rpm.</cod=
e><code class=3D"bash functions">tar</code><code class=3D"bash plain">.gz</=
code></div></div></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div>


<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img loading=3D"lazy=
" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1022" height=3D"727" src=3D"https://cdn.linux=
fordevices.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Extract-the-compressed-driver-fil=
es.png.webp" alt=3D"Extract The Compressed Driver Files" class=3D"wp-image-=
26216"><figcaption class=3D"wp-element-caption">Extract The Compressed Driv=
er Files</figcaption></figure>



<p>Note that you will have to change the name of the <code>tar.gz</code> fi=
le in the above command with the name of the file which you downloaded from=
 the website.</p>



<p>Once extracted, you have to execute the <code>install.sh</code> file fro=
m your Terminal with admin privileges and the driver will be installed on y=
our system. </p>



<p>You can do that simply by typing this command (again, do not forget to c=
hange the name of the extracted directory, just look into your Home folder =
from the file manager and copy-paste the new directory=E2=80=99s name after=
<a href=3D"https://www.linuxfordevices.com/tutorials/linux/cd-command-in-li=
nux" data-type=3D"post" data-id=3D"4661" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferre=
r noopener"> cd command</a>):</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-syntaxhighlighter-code "><div><div id=3D"highlighter=
_789410" class=3D"syntaxhighlighter  bash"><table border=3D"0" cellpadding=
=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"gutter"><div class=3D"line=
 number1 index0 alt2">1</div><div class=3D"line number2 index1 alt1">2</div=
></td><td class=3D"code"><div class=3D"container"><div class=3D"line number=
1 index0 alt2"><code class=3D"bash functions">cd</code> <code class=3D"bash=
 plain">cnijfilter2-6.00-1-rpm/</code></div><div class=3D"line number2 inde=
x1 alt1"><code class=3D"bash functions">sudo</code> <code class=3D"bash pla=
in">.</code><code class=3D"bash plain">/install</code><code class=3D"bash p=
lain">.sh</code></div></div></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div>


<figure class=3D"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img loading=3D"lazy=
" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1022" height=3D"727" src=3D"https://cdn.linux=
fordevices.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Make-sure-the-printer-is-on-and-c=
onnected-to-your-PC.png" alt=3D"Make Sure The Printer Is On And Connected T=
o Your PC" class=3D"wp-image-26218"><figcaption class=3D"wp-element-caption=
">Make Sure The Printer Is On And Connected To Your PC</figcaption></figure=
>



<p>Now, make sure that your printer is connected to your PC, either via USB=
 or over the network, and press Enter. You will be then asked several quest=
ions related to the printer, so answer them carefully step-by-step.</p><div=
 class=3D"code-block code-block-2" style=3D"margin: 8px 0; clear: both; hei=
ght: 250px;">
<div id=3D"dff5e9f6-d3ed-44f0-a9b9-9bac542719aa" class=3D"_ap_apex_ad" max-=
height=3D"250">
=09
</div>
